Step 3: Calculate the average total assets.  
• Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2

Step 4: Compute the Return on Assets (ROA).  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) × 100  
• ROA = (-1,401,436.89 / 13,544,930.33) × 100  
• ROA ≈ -10.35%

Thus, the calculated ROA is approximately -10.35%.
